## Expected Behavior 

The expected behavior is that the text highlighting cursor (and subsequently the available action) is only visible when hovering directly over text.  A great example is how the web handles text selection; Most things use the normal cursor, and only when directly over text will it allow you to highlight 

## Actual Behavior

The text highlighting cursor is shown for the entire area of SelectableText, which does not allow for page-turning via mouse grabbing gestures. This makes turning the page via the mouse impossible.

