issues.body:
For example, this app:

```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import 'package:flutter/widgets.dart';

void main() {
  final TextEditingController controller = TextEditingController();
  runApp(
    MaterialApp(
      home: Material(
        child: Center(
          child: Column(
            children: [
              TextField(controller: controller),
              TextButton(
                onPressed: () {
                  controller.text = 'abcdef' * 100000;
                },
                child: Text('Fill'),
              ),
            ],
          ),
        ),
      ),
    ),
  );
}
```

on my MacBook pro causes the app to freeze after pressing fill. I discovered this when accidentally pasting a very large amount of text into a text field while testing something else. In that case, the text field probably also had some extra styling and input formatters, and the app completely hung (and hot restarting caused it to crash). This sample app does not crash on hot restart, but I suspect adding formatters or making the text even larger might cause it to.

